name: datastore
title: Google Cloud Datastore API
description: Stores and queries data in Google Cloud Datastore.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: mutationResult
fields.desc: The result of performing the mutation (if any).

schemas.name: Key
schemas.desc: A unique identifier for an entity.

fields.name: partitionId
fields.desc: Entities are partitioned into subsets, currently identified by a dataset (usually implicitly specified by the project) and namespace ID. Queries are scoped to a single partition.

fields.name: path
fields.desc: The entity path. An entity path consists of one or more elements composed of a kind and a string or numerical identifier, which identify entities. The first element identifies a root entity, the second element identifies a child of the root entity, the third element a child of the second entity, and so forth. The entities identified by all prefixes of the path are called the element's ancestors. An entity path is always fully complete: ALL of the entity's ancestors are required to be in the path along with the entity identifier itself. The only exception is that in some documented cases, the identifier in the last path element (for the entity) itself may be omitted. A path can never be empty. The path can have at most 100 elements.

schemas.name: PropertyOrder
schemas.desc: The desired order for a specific property.

fields.name: direction
fields.desc: The direction to order by. One of ascending or descending. Optional, defaults to ascending.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to order by.

schemas.name: PropertyReference
schemas.desc: A reference to a property relative to the kind expressions.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the property.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc: A list of keys with incomplete key paths to allocate IDs for. No key may be reserved/read-only.

fields.name: isolationLevel
fields.desc: The transaction isolation level. Either snapshot or serializable. The default isolation level is snapshot isolation, which means that another transaction may not concurrently modify the data that is modified by this transaction. Optionally, a transaction can request to be made serializable which means that another transaction cannot concurrently modify the data that is read or modified by this transaction.

fields.name: multi
fields.desc: If this property contains a list of values. Input values may explicitly set multi to false, but otherwise false is always represented by omitting multi.

fields.name: values
fields.desc: The value(s) of the property. When multi is false there is always exactly one value. When multi is true there are always one or more values. Each value can have only one value property populated. For example, you cannot have a values list of { values: [ { integerValue: 22, stringValue: "a" } ] }, but you can have { multi: true, values: [ { integerValue: 22 }, { stringValue: "a" } ] }.

fields.name: offset
fields.desc: The number of results to skip. Applies before limit, but after all other constraints (optional, defaults to 0).

fields.name: order
fields.desc: The order to apply to the query results (if empty, order is unspecified).

fields.name: projection
fields.desc: The projection to return. If not set the entire entity is returned.

fields.name: startCursor
fields.desc: A starting point for the query results. Optional. Query cursors are returned in query result batches.

fields.name: kinds
fields.desc: The kinds to query (if empty, returns entities from all kinds).

fields.name: limit
fields.desc: The maximum number of results to return. Applies after all other constraints. Optional.

fields.name: groupBy
fields.desc: The properties to group by (if empty, no grouping is applied to the result set).

fields.name: endCursor
fields.desc: An ending point for the query results. Optional. Query cursors are returned in query result batches.

fields.name: filter
fields.desc: The filter to apply (optional).

fields.name: readConsistency
fields.desc: The read consistency to use. One of default, strong, or eventual. Cannot be set when transaction is set. Lookup and ancestor queries default to strong, global queries default to eventual and cannot be set to strong. Optional. Default is default.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc: The transaction to use. Optional.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc: The transaction identifier, returned by a call to beginTransaction.

schemas.name: Value
schemas.desc: A message that can hold any of the supported value types and associated metadata.

fields.name: stringValue
fields.desc: A UTF-8 encoded string value. When indexed is true, may have at most 500 characters.

fields.name: blobValue
fields.desc: A blob value. May be a maximum of 1,000,000 bytes. When indexed is true, may have at most 500 bytes.

fields.name: booleanValue
fields.desc: A boolean value.

fields.name: entityValue
fields.desc: An entity value. May have no key. May have a key with an incomplete key path. May have a reserved/read-only key.

fields.name: indexed
fields.desc:
If the value should be indexed.

The indexed property may be set for a null value. When indexed is true, stringValue is limited to 500 characters and the blob value is limited to 500 bytes. Input values by default have indexed set to true; however, you can explicitly set indexed to true if you want. (An output value never has indexed explicitly set to true.) If a value is itself an entity, it cannot have indexed set to true.

fields.name: integerValue
fields.desc: An integer value.

fields.name: keyValue
fields.desc: A key value.

fields.name: meaning
fields.desc: The meaning field is reserved and should not be used.

fields.name: blobKeyValue
fields.desc: A blob key value.

fields.name: dateTimeValue
fields.desc: A timestamp value.

fields.name: doubleValue
fields.desc: A double value.

schemas.name: GqlQueryArg
schemas.desc: A binding argument for a GQL query.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Must match regex "[A-Za-z_$][A-Za-z_$0-9]*". Must not match regex "__.*__". Must not be "".

fields.name: readOptions
fields.desc: Options for this lookup request. Optional.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc: Keys of entities to look up from the datastore.

fields.name: mutationResult
fields.desc: The result of performing the mutation (always present).

schemas.name: PartitionId
schemas.desc:
An identifier for a particular subset of entities.

Entities are partitioned into various subsets, each used by different datasets and different namespaces within a dataset and so forth.

fields.name: datasetId
fields.desc: The dataset ID.

fields.name: namespace
fields.desc: The namespace.

fields.name: gqlQuery
fields.desc: The GQL query to run. Either this field or field query must be set, but not both.

fields.name: partitionId
fields.desc: Entities are partitioned into subsets, identified by a dataset (usually implicitly specified by the project) and namespace ID. Queries are scoped to a single partition. This partition ID is normalized with the standard default context partition ID, but all other partition IDs in RunQueryRequest are normalized with this partition ID as the context partition ID.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: The query to run. Either this field or field gql_query must be set, but not both.

fields.name: readOptions
fields.desc: The options for this query.

fields.name: batch
fields.desc: A batch of query results (always present).

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc: The transaction identifier (always present).

fields.name: allowLiteral
fields.desc: When false, the query string must not contain a literal.

fields.name: nameArgs
fields.desc: A named argument must set field GqlQueryArg.name. No two named arguments may have the same name. For each non-reserved named binding site in the query string, there must be a named argument with that name, but not necessarily the inverse.

fields.name: numberArgs
fields.desc: Numbered binding site @1 references the first numbered argument, effectively using 1-based indexing, rather than the usual 0. A numbered argument must NOT set field GqlQueryArg.name. For each binding site numbered i in query_string, there must be an ith numbered argument. The inverse must also be true.

fields.name: queryString
fields.desc: The query string.

schemas.name: KeyPathElement
schemas.desc:
A (kind, ID/name) pair used to construct a key path.

At most one of name or ID may be set. If either is set, the element is complete. If neither is set, the element is incomplete.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the entity. Never equal to zero. Values less than zero are discouraged and will not be supported in the future.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of the entity. A kind matching regex "__.*__" is reserved/read-only. A kind must not contain more than 500 characters. Cannot be "".

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the entity. A name matching regex "__.*__" is reserved/read-only. A name must not be more than 500 characters. Cannot be "".

schemas.name: PropertyFilter
schemas.desc: A filter on a specific property.

fields.name: operator
fields.desc: The operator to filter by. One of lessThan, lessThanOrEqual, greaterThan, greaterThanOrEqual, equal, or hasAncestor.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to filter by.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value to compare the property to.

fields.name: mutation
fields.desc: The mutation to perform.

schemas.name: CompositeFilter
schemas.desc: A filter that merges the multiple other filters using the given operation.

fields.name: filters
fields.desc: The list of filters to combine. Must contain at least one filter.

fields.name: operator
fields.desc: The operator for combining multiple filters. Only "and" is currently supported.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc: The entity's properties.

fields.name: key
fields.desc:
The entity's key.

An entity must have a key, unless otherwise documented (for example, an entity in Value.entityValue may have no key). An entity's kind is its key's path's last element's kind, or null if it has no key.

fields.name: deferred
fields.desc: A list of keys that were not looked up due to resource constraints.

fields.name: found
fields.desc: Entities found.

fields.name: missing
fields.desc: Entities not found, with only the key populated.

schemas.name: Mutation
schemas.desc: A set of changes to apply.

fields.name: upsert
fields.desc: Entities to upsert. Each upserted entity's key must have a complete path and must not be reserved/read-only.

fields.name: delete
fields.desc: Keys of entities to delete. Each key must have a complete key path and must not be reserved/read-only.

fields.name: force
fields.desc: Ignore a user specified read-only period. Optional.

fields.name: insert
fields.desc: Entities to insert. Each inserted entity's key must have a complete path and must not be reserved/read-only.

fields.name: insertAutoId
fields.desc: Insert entities with a newly allocated ID. Each inserted entity's key must omit the final identifier in its path and must not be reserved/read-only.

fields.name: update
fields.desc: Entities to update. Each updated entity's key must have a complete path and must not be reserved/read-only.

schemas.name: PropertyExpression
schemas.desc: A representation of a property in a projection.

fields.name: aggregationFunction
fields.desc: The aggregation function to apply to the property. Optional. Can only be used when grouping by at least one property. Must then be set on all properties in the projection that are not being grouped by. Aggregation functions: first selects the first result as determined by the query's order.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to project.

schemas.name: QueryResultBatch
schemas.desc: A batch of results produced by a query.

fields.name: endCursor
fields.desc: A cursor that points to the position after the last result in the batch. May be absent. TODO(arfuller): Once all plans produce cursors update documentation here.

fields.name: entityResultType
fields.desc: The result type for every entity in entityResults. full for full entities, projection for entities with only projected properties, keyOnly for entities with only a key.

fields.name: entityResults
fields.desc: The results for this batch.

fields.name: moreResults
fields.desc: The state of the query after the current batch. One of notFinished, moreResultsAfterLimit, noMoreResults.

fields.name: skippedResults
fields.desc: The number of results skipped because of Query.offset.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc: The keys specified in the request (in the same order), each with its key path completed with a newly allocated ID.

schemas.name: EntityResult
schemas.desc: The result of fetching an entity from the datastore.

fields.name: entity
fields.desc: The resulting entity.

schemas.name: Filter
schemas.desc: A holder for any type of filter. Exactly one field should be specified.

fields.name: propertyFilter
fields.desc: A filter on a property.

fields.name: compositeFilter
fields.desc: A composite filter.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the kind.

fields.name: indexUpdates
fields.desc: Number of index writes.

fields.name: insertAutoIdKeys
fields.desc: Keys for insertAutoId entities. One per entity from the request, in the same order.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc: The transaction identifier, returned by a call to beginTransaction. Must be set when mode is TRANSACTIONAL.

fields.name: mutation
fields.desc: The mutation to perform. Optional.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "datastore#responseHeader".

methods.name: allocateIds
methods.desc: Allocate IDs for incomplete keys (useful for referencing an entity before it is inserted).

methods.name: blindWrite
methods.desc: Create, delete or modify some entities outside a transaction.

methods.name: commit
methods.desc: Commit a transaction, optionally creating, deleting or modifying some entities.

methods.name: lookup
methods.desc: Look up some entities by key.
